ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Time at first click
Time at last click
Time at scale submission
(Total) Number of clicks during scale completion
Total timing/time to complete scale
Quality Control (QC) (total) number of items (completed)
Quality Control (QC) (total) number of non-response items
On average, how often per year were you absent from school due to illness?
Notes: 1 = 0-4 days; 2= 5-9 days; 3= 10-14 days; 4= 15-19 days; 5= 20 or more days; 999 = Prefer not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: On average, how often per year were you sent to the nurse's office due to illness?
Notes: 1 = 0-4 days; 2= 5-9 days; 3= 10-14 days; 4= 15-19 days; 5= 20 or more days; 999 = Prefer not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did you have illnesses/symptoms such as headaches or stomachaches for which the doctors could not find a cause?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Rarely; 3=Sometimes; 4=Often; 5=Very Often; 999 = Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: How often do you have nightmares?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Once a year; 3=Once a month; 4=Once a week; 5=Every night; 999 = Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Were you scared of the dark?
Was it necessary for you or your parents to check under your bed or in your closet before you went to sleep?
Did you need to have a special stuffed animal, blanket, or toy with you so that you could fall asleep?
Were you afraid of dogs, cats, or other domestic animals?
Were you afraid of unfamiliar animals, such as those you encountered on the street or at someone else's home?
Were you scared that you would be kidnapped or otherwise separated from your parents?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Rarely; 3=Sometimes; 4=Often; 5=Very Often; 999 = Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did it upset you when your parents left you with a new, unfamiliar baby-sitter?
When your parents went out without you, were you scared that they might not come back?
Did you sleep over at friends' houses? (Reverse coded)
Notes: 1=Very Often; 2=Often; 3=Sometimes; 4=Rarely; 5=Never; 999 = Prefer Not to answer/left blank.

ElementDescription: Did you try new foods? (Reverse coded)
Notes: 1=Eagerly; 2=Agreeably; 3=With coaxing; 4=Only if pressured; 5= Never; 999 = prefer Not to answer/left blank.

ElementDescription: Were you usually scared on the first day of a new school year?
Notes: 1=Not at all; 2= Slightly; 3=Moderately; 4=Very; 5=Terrified; 999=Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did you ever pretend to be sick in order to avoid going to school or to social events?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Rarely; 3=Sometimes; 4=Often; 5=Very Often; 999 = Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did it upset you to be called up to the blackboard?
Notes: 1=Not at all; 2= Slightly; 3=Moderately; 4=Very; 5=Extremely; 999=Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did it upset you to be called on, even if you knew the answer?
Notes: 1=Not at all; 2= Slightly; 3=Moderately; 4=Very; 5=Extremely; 999=Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did your teachers have trouble hearing you when you spoke or answered a question in class?
If there was something you did not understand in class, did you ask the teacher for help? (Reverse coded)
During recess, did you play with the main group of children? (Reverse coded)
Did you enjoy participating in party games? (Reverse coded)
Did you enjoy meeting new children your age? (Reverse coded)
Did your voice squeak, crack, or sound shaky when you were talking in front of a group of people?
How popular did you feel? (Reverse coded)
Notes: 1=Very; 2=Moderately; 3=Average; 4=Below average; 5=Not at all; 999= Prefer Not to answer/left blank.

ElementDescription: Did you have any problems with, or have to see a doctor for allergies, sleeplessness, or constipation?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Rarely; 3=Sometimes; 4=Often; 5=Very Often; 999 = Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did you need a night-light or hall light on in order to go to sleep?
Did you willingly participate in group singing or plays? (Reverse coded)
Were your feelings easily hurt?
Notes: 1=Never; 2=Rarely; 3=Sometimes; 4=Often; 5=Very Often; 999 = Prefer Not to answer/left blank

ElementDescription: Did you tell your friends or family members when you were angry with them? (Reverse coded)
